    "memFaultInjectButton": { "nodeId": "ram", "addr": 5, "stuckAt": 1, "bit": null, "label": "Corrupt RAM cell 5 (whole-word stuck-at-1)" },
    "_doc": "Simple CPU + COMPLETE DFT stack: scan + MISR + LBIST loop + memory-BIST — the crown-jewel interview showcase.\n\n  CORE (unchanged single-cycle CPU):\n    PC → ROM → IR → CU → ALU ↔ REG_FILE_DP (RF) ↔ RAM (via TEST_MODE collar).\n\n  PRE-LOADED REGISTERS: R0=0 R1=5 R2=1 R3=0 R4=7 R5=3 R6=99 R7=0.\n  PROGRAM (8 instructions): accumulates R3, stores to mem[3], loops on R1\n  with BNE (4× taken + 1× not-taken), loads back, never-taken BEQ, HALT.\n\n  DFT STACK (5 layers, all on one canvas):\n    1. SCAN CHAIN — 4 SCAN_FFs, TE forces shift mode. In LBIST mode the\n       chain's serial-in is sourced from the LFSR; in functional mode it\n       comes from the SCAN_IN pad. Selection via LBIST_MUX (sel=LBIST_MODE_EN).\n    2. MISR — 8-bit signature compactor. D[0] = SCAN_OUT (chain integrity\n       observation); D[1..7] = RF_A[1..7] (functional observation, so faults\n       in CU/ALU/RF propagate to the signature).\n    3. LOGIC BIST (LBIST) — BIST_CTRL FSM runs 24 cycles, then samples\n       MISR and compares to goldenSig=0x03. Match → DONE/PASS.\n    4. LFSR_ATPG — free-running 8-bit Fibonacci LFSR (taps 7,5,4,3,\n       period 255) feeding the scan chain in LBIST mode.\n    5. MEMORY BIST — MBIST_CONTROLLER walks the RAM through March C−\n       via a 4-MUX TEST_MODE collar. Pre-injected cell fault at addr=5\n       (whole-word stuck-at-1) so the demo runs to FAIL.\n\n  LBIST LOOP (the closed test path):\n    LFSR → LBIST_MUX → SCAN_IN → S0 → S1 → S2 → S3 → MISR.D0\n         (parallel: RF_A[1..7] → MISR.D[1..7])\n    With clean logic the 24-cycle MISR signature is 0x03; the BIST_CTRL\n    compares and lands on PASS. With a fault, the signature diverges and\n    the controller lands on FAIL.\n\n  THREE-BUTTON DEMO FLOW (the interview narrative):\n    🔬 SHOW DFT LAYER — reveal the entire test collar wrapped around the CPU.\n    🐞 INJECT FAULT   — stuck-at-0 on CU.REG_WE → LBIST signature diverges → FAIL.\n    💥 CORRUPT CELL   — RAM cell 5 stuck-at-1 → MBIST hits FAIL at failAddr=5.\n  Each fault is toggleable: click again to clear.\n\n  HOW TO RUN (interview script):\n    a) Press RUN. With everything clean: LBIST reaches DONE/PASS within\n       ~26 ticks (MISR signature = 0x03 matches goldenSig), MBIST walks\n       March C− and reaches DONE/PASS after ~243 ticks.\n    b) Open DFT panel (T) — note both controllers (BIST_CTRL + MBIST)\n       both showing green PASS pills.\n    c) **LBIST fault**: click red 🐞 INJECT FAULT — stuck-at-0 forced on\n       CU.REG_WE wire. Pulse BIST_RESET. Within 26 ticks: signature\n       becomes 0x99, BIST_CTRL → FAIL (red lamp). Click 🐞 again → clean.\n    d) **MBIST fault**: click purple 💥 CORRUPT CELL — installs a\n       whole-word stuck-at-1 fault on RAM cell 5 (visible as a red\n       chip in the CELL FAULTS grid). Pulse MBIST_RESET. Around tick\n       ~36 MBIST reaches FAIL with failAddr=5. Click 💥 again → clean.\n    e) Both at once: click both buttons → both controllers FAIL on the\n       same run, showing logic-BIST and memory-BIST are independent.\n    f) For scan-only: TE=1 + LBIST_MODE_EN=0, step the clock manually."
  },
